      "agentResultText": "Build passes cleanly. Here's what was implemented:\n\n### Transactional move query (`src/lib/db/queries.ts`)\n`moveTask(taskId, fromProjectId, toProjectId)` uses `db.transaction()` to:\n1. Verify the task exists in the source project\n2. Verify the destination project exists\n3. Update `tasks.projectId` to the new project\n\nAll three steps run in a single transaction — if any check fails, the whole operation rolls back.\n\n### API endpoint (`POST /api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/move`)\n- Accepts `{ targetProjectId }` in the request body\n- Returns 400 if no valid target or same project\n- Returns 404 if task or destination project not found\n- Returns the updated task on success\n\n### UI (`src/components/move-task.tsx`)\nEach task row now has an **Actions** column with a \"Move\" button that:\n1. Expands into a project dropdown (filtered to exclude the current project) + \"Go\"/\"✕\" buttons\n2. POSTs to the move endpoint and calls `router.refresh()` to update the page",
