      "agentResultText": "Here's what was implemented:\n\n### Schema change\n- Added nullable `archivedAt` timestamp column to `tasks` table with a generated migration (`drizzle/0001_damp_absorbing_man.sql`)\n\n### Query layer (`src/lib/db/queries.ts`)\n- **All existing queries** now filter out archived tasks with `isNull(tasks.archivedAt)` — this covers `getTasksForProject`, `getFilteredTasks`, `getProjectsWithTaskCount`, `getTaskCountForProject`, `getAllTasks`, `getTaskStatusCounts`, and `getDashboardStats`\n- **`archiveTask(taskId, projectId)`** — sets `archivedAt` to now, only if task is currently active\n- **`restoreTask(taskId, projectId)`** — sets `archivedAt` to null, only if task is currently archived\n- **`getArchivedTasks(projectId)`** — returns tasks where `archivedAt IS NOT NULL`\n\n### API endpoints\n- **`POST /api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/archive`** — archives a task, returns 404 if not found\n- **`POST /api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/restore`** — restores an archived task, returns 404 if not found\n\n### UI\n- **Project detail page** — each task row now has an \"Archive\" button alongside \"Move\"\n- **Archived tasks page** (`/projects/[id]/archived`) — shows a full table of archived tasks with status, priority, assignee, archive date, and a \"Restore\" button per row. Shows \"No archived tasks.\" when empty.",
